The paper deals with information-theoretic lower bounds and efficient algorithms for group testing, which involves testing multiple items simultaneously to identify which ones are defective. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT), as well as algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
